  "prompt": "Which is the best brand of whisky in India?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" whisky brand in India can be subjective, as it often depends on personal preferences regarding taste, style, and budget. However, some of the most popular and highly regarded whisky brands in India include:\n\n1. **Amrut** - Known for its single malt whiskies, Amrut has garnered international acclaim and is often considered one of the best Indian whiskies.\n\n2. **Paul John** - Another premium single malt brand from Goa, Paul John offers a range of expressions that have received positive reviews globally.\n\n3. **Woodburns** - This brand is gaining popularity for its unique flavor profiles and artisanal approach to whisky making.\n\n4. **Blenders Pride** - A well-known brand for blending, Blenders Pride has a loyal following and is widely available in India.\n\n5. **Royal Challenge** - Known for its smoothness and affordability, it\u2019s a popular choice among whisky drinkers in India.\n\n6. **Macallan** - While originally a Scottish brand, Macallan has a strong presence in India and is often sought after for its quality.\n\n7. **Rampur** - This Indian single malt whisky is known for its rich flavors and has been recognized in several tasting competitions.\n\nUltimately, the best whisky for you will depend on your taste preferences, whether you enjoy blends, single malts, or specific flavor profiles. It's worth trying different brands and expressions to find out which one you prefer.",
